    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838\"><html>\n  <head>\n    \n  </head>\n  \n    <br>\n    <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838moz-cite-prefix\">On 2/23/2015 1:03 PM, David Saff\n      <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838moz-txt-link-abbreviated\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:saff@...\">saff@...</a> [junit] wrote:<br>\n    </div>\n    <blockquote><span title=\"qreply\"> <blockquote\n\n type=\"cite\"> <span style=\"display:none;\"> </span>\n      \n          <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-text\">\n            <div dir=\"ltr\">For what it&#39;s worth, I&#39;ve often found that\n              it&#39;s easy to optimize test hierarchies too quickly.  I&#39;ll\n              often focus first on factoring common code so that my test\n              cases can be succinct:\n              <div><br>\n              </div>\n              <div>@Test public void testNormalBoardHas4Corners() {</div>\n              <div>  assertEquals(4, NORMAL_BOARD.numCorners());</div>\n              <div>}</div>\n              <div><br>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n                <div>@Test public void testMoebiusBoardHas0Corners() {</div>\n                <div>  assertEquals(0, MOEBIUS_BOARD.numCorners());</div>\n                <div>}</div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        \n      \n    </blockquote>\n    yes. i agree. will do.<br>\n    <blockquote\n\n type=\"cite\">\n      <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-mlmsg\" style=\"\">\n        <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-msg\" style=\"\">\n          <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-text\">\n            <div dir=\"ltr\">\n              <div>The one thing that can be annoying in these cases is\n                keeping the test names interesting and accurate.  But I\n                find that it&#39;s much easier to come back to tests written\n                in this way 6 months later and remember what they&#39;re\n                doing than it is when using a more complicated hierarchy\n                or parameters-based approach.</div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </blockquote>\n    yes, that is one big advantage.<br>\n    <br>\n    thanks<br>\n    <blockquote\n\n type=\"cite\">\n      <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-mlmsg\" style=\"\">\n        <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-msg\" style=\"\">\n          <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838ygrp-text\">\n            <div dir=\"ltr\"><br>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838gmail_extra\"><br>\n              <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838gmail_quote\">On Sat, Feb 21, 2015 at 10:17 PM,\n                <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:rtayek@...\">rtayek@...</a>\n                [junit] <span dir=\"ltr\">&lt;<a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com\">junit@yahoogroups.com</a>&gt;</span>\n                wrote:<br>\n                <blockquote class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838gmail_quote\" style=\"border-left:1px #ccc solid;\">\n                  <div style=\"background-color:#fff;\">\n                    <span> </span>\n                    <div>\n                      <div>\n                        <div>\n                          <p>hi, i am writing a program that lets two\n                            players play a game of <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_%28game%29\"\n>Go (game) - Wikipedia, the\n                              free encyclopedia</a></p>\n                          <div style=\"width:450px;\">\n                            <table\n style=\"width:450px;height:170px;margin-top:5px;margin-bottom:5px;\"\n cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n                              <tbody>\n                                <tr>\n                                  <td colspan=\"6\"\n style=\"height:1px;background-color:#e5e5e5;\">\n                                    <br>\n                                  </td>\n                                </tr>\n                                <tr>\n                                  <td rowspan=\"2\"\n style=\"width:1px;background-color:#e5e5e5;\">\n                                    <br>\n                                  </td>\n                                  <td rowspan=\"2\"\n style=\"vertical-align:middle;width:168px;height:168px;background-color:#000000;\">\n                                    <div style=\"width:168px;\"\n align=\"center\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n\n\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_%28game%29\"\n style=\"text-decoration:none;color:#000000;\"> <img\n\n alt=\"image\"\n src=\"https://ec.yimg.com/ec?url=http%3A%2F%2Fupload.wikimedia.org%2Fwikipedia%2Fcommons%2Fthumb%2Ff%2Ff3%2FGo-board-animated.gif%2F220px-Go-board-animated.gif&t=1572967126&sig=3bwT2vjkmL5aHVerzam3Pg--~E\"\n style=\"margin:auto;\"\n height=\"168\" width=\"168\"> </a>\n                                    </div>\n                                  </td>\n                                  <td rowspan=\"2\"\n style=\"width:1px;background-color:#e5e5e5;\">\n                                    <br>\n                                  </td>\n                                  <td colspan=\"2\"\n style=\"width:100%;vertical-align:middle;\">\n                                    <div\n style=\"background-color:#ffffff;min-height:130px;width:279px;\">\n                                      <div style=\"padding:7px 20px 0px 14px;\"> <span></span> <span></span>\n                                        <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_%28game%29\"\n style=\"text-decoration:none;color:#000000;\"> <span\n style=\"margin:0;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:4px;font-size:18px;max-height:43px;color:#000000;overflow:hidden;\">Go\n                                            (game) - Wikipedia, the free\n                                            encyclopedia</span> </a>\n                                        <div\n style=\"font-size:13px;color:#999999;max-height:81px;overflow:hidden;\">Go\n                                          (simplified Chinese: 围棋;\n                                          traditional Chinese: 圍棋;\n                                          pinyin: wéiqí, Japanese: 囲碁\n                                          igo,[nb 2] literal meaning:\n                                          &quot;encircling game&quot;, Korean: 바둑\n                                          baduk[nb 3]) is...</div>\n                                      </div>\n                                    </div>\n                                  </td>\n                                  <td rowspan=\"2\"\n style=\"width:1px;background-color:#e5e5e5;\">\n                                    <br>\n                                  </td>\n                                </tr>\n                                <tr>\n                                  <td\n style=\"width:100%;vertical-align:middle;\">\n                                    <div\n style=\"font-size:0pt;padding:7px 20px 9px 15px;\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n\n\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_%28game%29\"\n style=\"color:black;text-decoration:none;\"> <span\n style=\"max-width:179px;min-width:119px;overflow:hidden;max-height:13px;\">\n                                          <span\n style=\"vertical-align:middle;font-size:9px;color:#999999;\">\n                                            View on <span\n style=\"font-weight:bold;\">en.wikipedia.org</span>\n                                          </span> </span> </a> </div>\n                                  </td>\n                                  <td\n style=\"vertical-align:middle;width:100px;\">\n                                    <div style=\"padding:9px 20px 12px 0px;max-width:100px;min-width:80px;overflow:hidden;text-align:right;max-height:13px;font-size:0pt;\">\n                                      <span\n style=\"vertical-align:middle;font-size:9px;color:#999999;\">\n                                        Preview by Yahoo </span> </div>\n                                  </td>\n                                </tr>\n                                <tr>\n                                  <td colspan=\"6\"\n style=\"height:1px;background-color:#e5e5e5;\">\n                                    <br>\n                                  </td>\n                                </tr>\n                              </tbody>\n                            </table>\n                          </div>\n                          <p>  </p>\n                          on unusual go boards. some of the boards may\n                          have unusual shapes or have holes or have a\n                          strange topology (cylinder, torus). these\n                          boards will have some unusual features (not\n                          quite sure if i am using the work <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://xunitpatterns.com/feature.html\"\n>feature</a> correctly here).<br>\n                          <br>\n                          but my real problem is that i have a lot of\n                          test fixtures. these are boards of different\n                          sizes, shapes, holes and topology.<br>\n                          <br>\n                          i have an abstract test case (atc) for the\n                          board interface, and concrete test case\n                          (subclass of atc) for the board implementation\n                          (impltc) and a couple feature test cases\n                          (subclasses of impltc) with not much in them\n                          now. <br>\n                          <br>\n                          the concrete test case creates a standard\n                          19x19 board in setup (fixture) for some of the\n                          tests to use. but <span\n style=\"font-style:italic;\">many</span> of\n                          the tests create <span\n style=\"font-style:italic;\">many</span>\n                          boards. many of these boards are not changed,\n                          but some are (maybe i need an interface for an\n                          immutable board?).<br>\n                          <br>\n                          in any case, many of the fixtures are being\n                          created many times. while not particularly\n                          slow, i feel that there may be a way to\n                          organize the test case class hierarchy for\n                          boards.<br>\n                          <br>\n                          maybe a parameterised test case with a bunch\n                          of boards? or maybe one for normal boards and\n                          one for unusual boards?<br>\n                          <br>\n                          i just ran across <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://xunitpatterns.com/Testcase%20Class%20per%20Fixture.html\"\n>test case per fixture</a>\n                          and <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://xunitpatterns.com/Testcase%20Class%20per%20Feature.html\"\n>test case per feature</a> so\n                          i am a little confused.<br>\n                          <br>\n                          any pointers will be appreciated.<br>\n                          <br>\n                          thanks<br>\n                          <p><span><br>\n                            </span></p>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                </blockquote>\n              </div>\n              <br>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          \n      \n      \n    </div></div></blockquote>\n    <br>\n    <pre class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838moz-signature\">-- \nHonesty is a very expensive gift. So, don&#39;t expect it from cheap people - Warren Buffet﻿\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-70735838moz-txt-link-freetext\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://tayek.com/\">http://tayek.com/</a></pre>\n  \n</span></blockquote></html>\n</div>", 
